(49081, 118740, 4511, 3, 'Albert Einstein', '把愛因斯坦唱成歌了！\r\n嗯，或許哲學家會比宗教家喜歡，而物理老師們會比音樂老師們更有興趣吧？\r\n\r\n＊另有大國小雪合唱版\r\nhttp://www.indievox.com/song/49233\r\n', '2012-06-08 00:00:00', 2012, 20, 0, 6, 'Albert Einstein\r\n詞/曲/演唱　大國Gordon Tseng　　編曲　小雪Sharon Tseng\r\n\r\n\r\nWhatever the observer may observe in whatever place,\r\nIt is believed that all scientific rules have the same base.\r\nSo, the universe is understandable and works with a grace\r\nThat surprised Albert, who later surprised the human race.\r\n\r\nSince there are no absolute time and space,\r\nNewton’s apple has got a relative face.\r\nIf light always goes straight is not the case,\r\nAlbert surely is the one who set the world’s new pace. \r\n \r\nTo figure out how God created the world so reasonable and great,\r\nAlbert knew that quiet loneliness would be his inevitable fate.\r\nBut, he could never figure out why God just could not wait\r\nTo quiet him forever till his final theory finished debate.  \r\n\r\n\r\n（原詩Einstein(1) (2) (3)來自大國Gordon Tseng的英文四行詩集GOD BLESS NOT ONLY AMERICA）', '', 279, '', '大國Gordon Tseng', '大國Gordon Tseng', '大國Gordon Tseng', '', '', 0, 0, 0, '2012-06-08 18:24:20', '2015-03-12 13:53:05', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
